      "reviews": [
        {
          "reviewTitle": "Great Box Spring \u2014 Sturdy, Easy to Assemble",
          "reviewText": "I ordered this twin box spring to go with my new Firm-Gold mattress, and so far, I\u2019m very happy with it! I wanted everything brand new since I was finally replacing my old bed setup, and this box spring was a great choice. It came well-packaged, with all the parts neatly organized. Assembly was straightforward \u2014 I took my time while my mattress was decompressing and had it fully put together in under an hour. Once assembled, it felt sturdy and stable right away. I didn\u2019t notice any bending, creaking, or weak spots. The metal pieces fit together tightly, and I added a few zip ties where the metal meets metal, just to make sure there was zero movement or noise \u2014 and it\u2019s been completely silent ever since. The height is just right for now. I paired it with a 14\u201d mattress, and while the setup sits a little lower than I prefer, that\u2019s more about my frame being short. A set of bed risers will easily fix that later. I also used some leftover plywood cut to size on top of the box spring before placing the mattress, to make sure the surface was perfectly flat (memory foam can sag if not fully supported). That setup has worked perfectly so far. Overall, I\u2019m impressed \u2014 this box spring feels strong, supportive, and well-built. It was affordable, easy to assemble, and made a huge difference in how solid my new bed feels. If you\u2019re looking for a sturdy foundation without spending a fortune, this one\u2019s a great pick. Ps I love that the box spring cover is a fitted sheet deal so if I want (which I probably will a few times a year) I can wash it to make the room feel complete fresh.",
